THIRD-PARTY DEPENDENCY NOTICE

This software uses third-party libraries with their own licenses. When
distributing this software, container images, packaged builds or derivative
works, you must comply with the licenses of bundled dependencies as well as
this MIT license.

Key non-MIT or copyleft dependencies currently include:

  - scapy (https://scapy.net/) — GPL-2.0-only
    Used for: ARP network scanning
    Source: https://github.com/secdev/scapy

  - python-nmap (https://pypi.org/project/python-nmap/) — GPL-3.0
    Used for: Per-device port scanning
    Source: https://bitbucket.org/xael/python-nmap

  - paramiko (https://www.paramiko.org/) — LGPL-2.1
    Used for: SSH-related connectivity support
    Source: https://github.com/paramiko/paramiko

  - manuf (https://pypi.org/project/manuf/) — Apache-2.0 or GPL-3.0
    Used for: MAC vendor lookup data
    Source: https://github.com/coolbho3k/manuf

See THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.md for the dependency license matrix and
redistribution notes.
